<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id52a6ff51-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6" identifier="/us/usc/t28/s1401"><num value="1401">§ 1401.</num><heading> Stockholder’s derivative action</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Any civil action by a stockholder on behalf of his corporation may be prosecuted in any judicial district where the corporation might have sued the same defendants.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id52a6ff52-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6">(<ref href="/us/act/1948-06-25/ch646">June 25, 1948, ch. 646</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/62/936">62 Stat. 936</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id52a6ff53-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="historicalAndRevision" id="id52a6ff54-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Historical and Revision Notes</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Based on title 28, U.S.C., 1940 ed., § 112 (part) (<ref href="/us/act/1911-03-03/ch231/s51">Mar. 3, 1911, ch. 231, § 51</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/36/1101">36 Stat. 1101</ref>; <ref href="/us/act/1922-09-19/ch345">Sept. 19, 1922, ch. 345</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/42/849">42 Stat. 849</ref>; <ref href="/us/act/1925-03-04/ch526/s1">Mar. 4, 1925, ch. 526, § 1</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/43/1264">43 Stat. 1264</ref>; <ref href="/us/act/1936-04-16/ch230">Apr. 16, 1936, ch. 230</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/49/1213">49 Stat. 1213</ref>).</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">For disposition of other provisions of <ref href="/us/usc/t28/s112">section 112 of title 28</ref>, U.S.C., 1940 ed., see reviser’s note under <ref href="/us/usc/t28/s1391">section 1391 of this title</ref>.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Words “civil action” were substituted for “suit,” in view of Rule 2 of the Federal Rules of Civil Procedure.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Words “other than said corporation,” after “same defendants,” were omitted as superfluous. Obviously a corporation would not be suing itself.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Changes were made in phraseology.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
